
o max_pitch, max_rudder, max_thrust, max_elevator
  Should we *require* that these be specified in the 
  configuration block, and fail to launch otherwise? Or
  are there reasonable defaults that can be used?

o When depth and/or altitude limits are exceeded by 
  "safe-ops" behaviors, what should the result be?
  a) DESIRED_THRUST = 0
  b) DESIRED_RUDDER = 0
  c) DESIRED_ELEVATOR = 0
  d) MOOS_MANUAL_OVERRIDE = TRUE

o Behavior Configuration

   Individual call to BHV_FOOBAR::setParam(string, string);

  (a) Each parameter/value pair is checked for proper syntax
      and semantics. 
  (b) If invalid upon startup of Helm, Helm will abort.
  (c) If invalid upon dynamic message, state_ok=false;

  Sequence of calls to BHV_FOOBAR::setParam(string, string);
  (1) Sequence is tested by a call to IvPBehavior::validParams()
  (2) If invalid upon startup of Helm, Helm will abort.
  (3) If invalid upon dynamic message, state_ok=false;

